<Issue id="26886" key="FABC-433" number="433" project="10607" reporter="smithbk" creator="smithbk" type="10001" summary="REST APIs for managing CAs and profiles" priority="3" status="10000" created="2018-01-17 19:51:17.0" updated="2019-07-27 14:59:30.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="32615"> <description><! CDATA Fabric CA should expose the following to read CA and profile info. It is read-only currently, but the APIs position us well to support write in the future if needed.  1) GET /api/v1/ca Returns a list of all CAs managed by the server, and the profiles for each CA.  Similar to: {code} { "ca": { "default": { "profile": { "default": { ... } } } } {code}  2) GET /api/v1/ca/<CAName> Returns info for a single CA named <CAName>  3) GET /api/v1/ca/<CAName>/profile Returns all profile info for a single CA name <CAName>  4) GET /api/v1/ca/<CAName>/profile/<profileName> Returns only info for profile <profileName> of CA <CAName>   ></description> </Issue>
